(6, 'Top 10 Reasons to Study in Canada', 'be95415a3c.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Top 10 Reasons to Study in Canada&lt;/h2&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Get a World - Class Experience from Top Universities in Canada:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Canadian colleges are the piece of art and it is accepted and tested by all. Be it in the technology sector, or in the non-tech counterpart, Canadians colleges are known to deliver a world-class education as it is proved by the fact that a total of six&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Canadian universities&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;have managed to get a place in the Top 100 rankings of the best universities all over the globe by the Times Higher Education World University Ratings, making them one of the best reasons to study in Canada. Moreover, education in Canada is on the affordable side compared to the other English speaking countries like the USA and Australia.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Here is the list of Universities in Canada with QS World Rankings:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;University of Toronto, Ontario&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(28th)&lt;/p&gt;\n	&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;McGill University, Montreal&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(33rd)&lt;/p&gt;\n	&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;University of British Columbia&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(47th)&lt;/p&gt;\n	&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;University of Alberta&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(109th)&lt;/p&gt;\n	&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;McMaster University&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(146th)&lt;/p&gt;\n	&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Check out more here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Universities in Canada&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Get on the High Road to Success to Experience the Tech Industry:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;There are very predominant industries in Canada such as telecommunications, video games, biotech, digital media and aeronautical engineering and MBA in Canada. Canada took&amp;nbsp;initiative and was one of the first countries to connect to the internet through an innovative SchoolNet program. Talking about the internet connectivity here, it would be a pretty amazing fact that almost 90% of Canadian households are connected to the internet. The technological programs and research output in Canadian Universities are commendable.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Experience and have a chance to learn multi-languages:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to boost your language and communication skills to a whole new level? If yes, then Canada might be the place for you because of its bilingual culture. The two of the major spoken languages of the world namely the French and the English are an integral part of the Canadian educational system.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Get a Sure Shot at Employment After Graduation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;This has to be one of the top 5 reasons to study in Canada. After getting a diploma from a post-secondary school the government of Canada offers a work program for&amp;nbsp;the students to Study Abroad. Thinking of ways to continue your stay in Canada to develop and diversify your professional skills? Well, the work program might be the answer to this question.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. Get a Taste of Excellent Lifestyle:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Three cities in Canada made it to the top 50 in the rankings of student cities to Study abroad, namely Toronto, Montreal, and Vancouver. The criteria for the rankings comprised of several factors such as the diversity of the student population, affordability and the perception of the employers for the graduates in the job market.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6. Work While Studying:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;A Canadian study permit allows international students to work while studying without having to apply for a separate work permit. International students can work at part-time jobs for 20 hours a week. Additionally, during semester breaks and summer breaks, they are allowed to work full time. Working while studying can prove to be a great opportunity for the students at having the work-experience and networking even before they graduate. However, it is not mandatory to have a part-time job in Canada in a particular field of study that the student is pursuing&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7. Immerse in the Natural Beauty of Canada:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Spread across a vast area which is roughly 14 times than that of France, Canada offers a magnificent landscape that is available to explore throughout the four seasons. There are a vast number of tourism sites in Canada such as:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;The fascinating Rockies&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;Lake Louise&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;Niagara Falls&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;Whistler Mountainâ€‹&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Now that you know all seven of them, what are you waiting for? Not only academically, Studying in Canada will help you develop your overall personality with a world-class education, research resources and best of the student life.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8. Safety:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Canada is one of the safest countries in the world, and you will realise that as soon as you land for the first time in the country. The colleges and universities take extra measures to make the environment safe for international student. &amp;nbsp;Along with that, Public Safety Canada is a government body created for all kind of risks to public safety.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9. Canada Immigration Policy:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Go through our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Student Visa&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in canada&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;Guidelines and you will know how straightforward and transparent the visa process is. Study and Work in Canada, Stay Back options and work after studies are one of the most liberal in the world. You can get as long as 3 years of Stay Back period once your studies are over. Students, many of them apply for permanent residency after that.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10. Not only Winters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;A common misconception is that Canada is just about harsh winters. Now, the winters are long and cold at places. However, they are as many as four seasons in Canada. The more you start coming to the South, the days are longer and winters are shorter. The spring and fall are the seasons to look forward too. Most of the courses also will start in fall, and you get to see Canada the way you had not imagined before.&lt;/p&gt;'),
(7, 'Canada Student Visa Rejection: Reasons and appeals', '0814cead2c.png', '&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Canada Student Visa Rejection Reasons&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;As per CIC, Canada student visa rejection rate is an average of 30% of the total student visa applications. There are various reasons why a Canadian study visa application may be rejected. These reasons will be mentioned in the refusal letter issued by visa authorities Below are the most common student visa rejection reasons for Canada :&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;1. Not enough Proof of Financial Support&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;When you submit a visa application, you need to demonstrate that you have sufficient funds to support yourself in Canada. Immigration Authorities require that all international students should prove they have sufficient funds to cover their tuition fees for the first year of study and the living cost for themselves. Your application will be refused if you are unable to prove the ability to financially support yourself.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;2. Doubt on Intention to Leave the Country&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;A study visa is a temporary visa, which means that it has a validity period and expiration date. In your visa application, you need to convince the visa officer that you will leave the country when your study permit expires. The visa officer must be convinced that you will not stay in Canada illegally when your visa expires. You should have good reasons to want to return back to your home country. The best way to address this concern is through your statement of purpose.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;3. Wrong Choice of Study Program&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Visa applications are sometimes rejected if the visa officer doesn&amp;rsquo;t understand the reason for choosing your study program or level of study. If the chosen program in Canada doesn&amp;rsquo;t seem to line up with the applicant&amp;rsquo;s educational background or employment history, the visa application can be rejected. For example, someone with a Bachelor&amp;rsquo;s Degree in Nursing and 4 years of working experience as a nurse wants to study hotel management in Canada, which could bring doubt, and hence visa application is rejected. If your study program seems odd, based on your past education you need to clearly explain why you want to study it in your statement of purpose.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;4. Incomplete Your Travel or Identity Documents&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;If you don&amp;rsquo;t have a complete record of your travel history, or if your identity documents are unclear, visa officers may refuse your visa application. If the visa officer thinks there are blank spaces in your travel history, they will review your travel documents and the visa officer&amp;rsquo;s notes to find which periods are problematic. Visa authorities will verify your identity through the documents to determine whether you are medically or criminally can be accepted to Canada or not.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;5. Poor Academic Performance&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Visa officers give importance to stability across the previous academic performance. But while good grades are vital in visa approval, it also extends to your English language ability. With a combination of uneven grades and a low score, a visa officer may doubt your ability to cope with the current education system in Canada. This is one of the reasons for rejection of student visa Canada.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;6. Incomplete application form&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;The most important document for the students applying for the Student Visa is the Canadian Student Visa Application Form. A lot of times, &amp;nbsp;students provide inaccurate information which becomes one of the student visa rejection reasons for Canada. Many times students may be tempted to misinterpret questions in the application form. Consequently, the chances of making mistakes are very high and should be avoided in all circumstances.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to do if Your Application is Refused&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;When a student visa application is rejected, it will be informed in a letter issued by the visa officer to the applicant. Within this letter, the visa officer will mention the reason(s) for rejection. There are two options for addressing the refusal:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appeal the decision:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;If the student believes that their visa application is complete and fulfilled all requirements and the study visa was refused incorrectly or unfairly, he or she can appeal the decision. Applicant should request to reconsider the application.&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Submit a new application:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;If the student believes that the reasons for visa rejection are valid, then then they have only one option. They will have to submit a new application. Applicants should be very careful this time with their application as it is their second chance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Both the appeal process and the resubmission process may take some time. The applicant should therefore be prepared to contact their university to request a modification to their planned start date if they will not be able to obtain a visa in time to start their study program on the originally planned date.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;Tips to Decrease the Chances of Student Visa Rejection for Canada&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Now that the main reasons for visa refusal are known, here are a few valuable tips you should follow to avoid the refusal of student visas:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;Make a list of the documents required for the visa application process. The complete list can be found on the official website of the Government of Canada.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;Carefully and completely fill each detail on the visa application form. Ensure that no response box is left blank.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;Make sure to upload a copy of the offer letter that you have received from the university in Canada.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;You must show enough evidence of finance to support your stay during your studies in Canada.&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;If you have work experience, salary slips or bank statements are to be submitted to prove it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;You should mention all travel histories and visa rejections (if any) in the visa file.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;Do not leave any questions unanswered on the CIC website while applying online.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n	&lt;li&gt;The statement of intent is vital which will introduce your profile to the visa officer. Mention the academic achievements and the purpose to study in Canada. This statement of purpose is crucial for the visa application. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;h2&gt;FAQ (Frequently Asked Questions)&lt;/h2&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;1. Why is Canada student visa rejected?&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Canadian student visa applications are often refused for some reason such as failure to prove adequate financial resources, proof of intent to leave after the program ends, questionable travel, identity documentation, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;2. Can I get Canada study visa after refusal?&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;If a student visa for Canada application is refused, you can apply again at any time, unless your decision letter says you can&amp;#39;t. If you file properly and with a complete document set, the chances of obtaining visa approval are high.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;3. Can my student visa get rejected?&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;If you don&amp;rsquo;t file a proper and complete visa application, there are high chances that your student visa can be rejected. However, there are various other reasons such as poor academic performance, lack of English language proficiency, failure to provide enough financial capabilities, etc. can lead to visa rejection.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;4. Why is my Canada student visa taking so long?&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;After applying for your Canadian study permit, the processing time may take up to 90 days, but it&amp;#39;s usually faster. Depending on the situation in your home country, the visa processing time can vary. Currently, visa processing timing has been affected by the burst of the COVID-19 pandemic. Due to several restrictions, many visa applications were delayed.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;5. Do I get a refund if my student visa is refused Canada?&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;If your visa application gets rejected then the embassy is not liable to refund any fee in any circumstances. The embassy charges a fee as a cost to recover their expenses on the process only.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;6. What can I do if my Canadian student visa is refused?&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;When a Canadian student visa is refused, you have two courses of action depending on the reasons for rejection. You can appeal for reconsideration if you feel the decision was incorrect. You can re-apply if you have missed out on any step in the first visa application process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h3&gt;7. What are the chances of getting Canada student visa?&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;While a significant proportion of applicants are successful in obtaining the student visa for Canada, yet a 27-28% rejection rate means near 100,000 students are denied to study in Canada. Make sure you fulfill all the requirements.'),
(8, 'Top Reasons to Study in USA', 'Top Reasons to Study in USA.png', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s like a trend now a day to study in&amp;nbsp;USA . Some might be going for fulfilling their dreams, some for their parent&amp;rsquo;s dream&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; Not just because it is the most powerful nation in the world but The Statue of Liberty, White House, Disneyland are some of the places and things which fascinate people all over the world.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;But Jeduka provides some important reasons for students why they should choose USA for their higher education.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexibility:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;We know that most of the students do &lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;engineering in India&lt;/span&gt; either by their own wish or because of their friends or family. But in case after a year if you don&amp;rsquo;t like engineering and want to change your stream then you will lose a year. But in US you can change your field without loss of a year. In US you can go for a major i.e. your major is undecided. After 2 years of attending classes in different streams you can select your major i.e. if you like engineering you can go for engineering as a major, if you like psychology you can go for psychology as a major and if you like both then you can go for both.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Versatility:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;There is versatility in the education. They will not only give you training in your own field as well as in different fields well. As for an example business undergrad should do some essential science lectures, engineering undergrad will do some essential business lectures. In this way student will hav