ifferent clubs like cultural club, sports club which makes their life active.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use of technology:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;Technology assumes a significant part in research and development And American colleges have ensured they don&amp;#39;t fall behind with regards to that of technology by acquainting new techniques and abilities. They make sure that each college is well equipped with all the machines, technologies and thus student can develop themselves.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;So, these were some important reasons which can add up to your reasons of going to USA.&lt;/p&gt;'),
(9, 'Study in USA Without IELTS', '1598527487_Study_in_USA_Without_IELTS.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;To Study in USA is the first and foremost preference of the students who are willing to Study Abroad even though the cost of studying in the USA being so high. As it provides quality education. However, there are some admission criteria for the Universities in USA that might demotivate them. One of them is IELTS test. English Language Proficiency is something many aspirants want to avoid. Here are your options if you want to &lt;strong&gt;Study in USA without IELTS&amp;nbsp;2021.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;First, let us tell you the process:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to study in USA without IELTS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px&quot;&gt;Step 1: Application Process to Study in USA without IELTS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Research and shortlist Universities and courses you want to study in USA you want to apply to.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;You can check University rankings and Eligibility Requirements on the websites of the universities.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Go through all the shortlisted Universities and choose which is best for you academically and career-wise.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;You need to apply online for the University of colleges in USA you have selected.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 2: Skype / Video Interviews&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Once you are shortlisted by the University, you will be asked for a personal Interview. This helps them to evaluate your proficiency in the &amp;nbsp;English language and also check your eagerness to get accepted at the Universities. To get admission to the USA without IELTS, you have to complete this interview in the best possible manner.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 3: Tuition Fees and Other Study in USA Costs:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;If you pass your Video Interview, you will get a letter of acceptance from the college you have applied to. It is to confirm that you have been accepted for the study program you were interested in. The next step is to pay your tuition fees for the program. For more information click: Cost of studying in USA&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px&quot;&gt;Step 4: Apply for Student Visa in USA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In the next step, you need to apply for your student visa. Can I get &lt;strong&gt;USA study visa without IELTS?&lt;/strong&gt; is one of the questions for the international students who want to pursue their education in USA without giving IELTS. The USA visa rules are surely getting stringent day by day, however, if one has enough grades and academic excellence to show for, &amp;nbsp;without IELTS study in USA then it is possible.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px&quot;&gt;USA without IELTS Study Visa Process&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;So, is IELTS required for a student visa in USA? If you have an international baccalaureate or have done previous studies in the English language, or from an English-speaking country, the USA student visa without the IELTS process is can be done. However, if you are not one of the above, there might be a series of questions you will have to answer at the visa interview unless you have been selected for a highly ranked university. so if you want without an IELTS USA study visa, it is possible but a bit complicated. You will need the following documents&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;A Valid Passport&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Recent passport size photograph&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Confirmation page of DS-160&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Form I -20&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Payment of application fees for SEVIS&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Letter of admission/confirmation from the University&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Proof of Monetary Funds&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Proof of Accommodation&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;CV&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Academic Transcripts&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Healthcare Cover&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Your University will make you inform you about the additional requirements if any.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility criteria to study without IELTS in USA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are some criteria you will have to fulfill in order to get admission at a University in USA without IELTS:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ol&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;First of all, if you are a native of an English Speaking Country, and English is your First Language, there is no need to take &lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;IELTS&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;TOEFL&lt;/span&gt; or any English Language Proficiency Test for that matter.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;If you have attended and completed any kind of academic studies for at least one year in the USA, you can be accepted at a university to study in USA without IELTS.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;There are some Intensive English Learning Programs that some Universities offer. Abbreviated as IELP, they work as substitutes for IELTS and TOEFL tests.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Just like IELP, there are some Summer Programs in USA that you can attend to make up for the lack of English Language Proficiency Proof and &lt;strong&gt;study in America without IELTS&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Some Universities in USA offer Bridge courses for students who do not meet the minimum English Language Requirements for direct admission in a course.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Some of the institutes will not ask for any English Language Proficiency proof if you have completed your secondary school education and/or bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree in the English Language.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ol&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Universities in USA without IELTS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Here are &lt;strong&gt;list of without IELTS universities in USA&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;where you can Study Abroad without IELTS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;table align=&quot;center&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;8&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;background-color:#99cc99; width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Universities in USA without IELTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;background-color:#99cc99; width:375px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alternative Requirements to Study in USA without IELTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;University of Colorado&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;If the student is a native of an English Speaking Country&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Have completed an academic year in USA as a student.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;Drexel University&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;University Preparation Summer Program (UPSP), and&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Bridge Program for International Students&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;University of Arkansas&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Intensive English Language Program (IELP)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;University of Dayton&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Intensive English Language Program (IELP)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;California State University&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Must have attended secondary schooling or above for three academic years in:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:.25in&quot;&gt;Virgin Islands &amp;amp; Wales, United Kingdom, Trinidad, South Africa, Scotland, Nigeria, New Zealand, Kenya, Jamaica, Ireland, Guyana, Ghana, Canada (except Qu&amp;eacute;bec), Botswana, Bermuda, Belize, Barbados, Bahamas, Australia, Antigua&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p&gt;In some cases with the same criteria: Norway &amp;amp; Singapore&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;University of New Orleans&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;UNO IELP 63+ in LGVR and 70+ in Writing&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;University of Delaware&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;ELI (English Language for Internationals)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:226px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000ff&quot;&gt;University of Iowa&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td style=&quot;width:375px&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:0.25in&quot;&gt;The minimum score in IELTS:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:0.25in&quot;&gt;Overall bands: 4.5, no less than 4.0 in each module for conditional admission;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p&gt;After that, compulsory attend IIEP: Iowa International English Program&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is ESL Course?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;ESL stands for English as Second Language, like IELP that is mentioned above, is an English language course for the non-native English Speaker. These courses cover English Grammar, Vocabulary, Pronunciation, and spelling. These courses help students in attaining the English language proficiency required for the course and works as an alternative to study in USA without IELTS.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;As there are many ways to get accepted conditionally in USA universities without fulfilling the English Language Proficiency Requirements, one has to keep in mind that the Eligibility Criteria for Universities in USA changes from course to course and University to University. Some might ask for IELTS, some might not. IELTS scores always add to your Visa Process as they are proof that you know the basics of the English Language when it comes to Reading, Writing, Listening and Speaking.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;But as we mentioned Getting admission as well as a student visa in USA without IELTS is a bit complicated. We suggest you take IELTS and then go to America for further studies. If you work hard, we are sure that you will get through the exam easily.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How many IELTS bands are required for USA Universities?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Before we dive into the universities to study in USA without IELTS, here are some of the usual requirements for IELTS at the universities in USA. The bachelor and Masters in USA&amp;nbsp;programs for full-time courses have requirements of 6 to 7.5 IELTS bands overall, and the requirements for IELTS band score for USA will change with particular courses and universities. There are a large number of IELTS 6 band universities in USA. Some universities also offer courses at lower IELTS requirements with ESL courses in USA.&lt;/p&gt;');

